    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>What is an NRI Home Loan?</h2>
          <p>An NRI home loan is a housing loan offered to Non-Resident Indians (NRIs) and Persons of Indian Origin (PIOs) who wish to purchase residential or commercial property in India. These loans are governed by FEMA (Foreign Exchange Management Act) regulations and are available from most Indian banks and housing finance companies. NRI home loans can be used to buy flats, independent houses, plots (with construction), or commercial properties in India.</p>
          <p>TrueCred Loan Expert specializes in NRI home loans, connecting overseas Indians with the best lending options. Our dedicated NRI desk understands the unique challenges — time zone differences, document attestation requirements, power of attorney needs, and FEMA compliance — and provides end-to-end support. We partner with 30+ banks including SBI, HDFC, ICICI, and Axis that have specialized NRI home loan divisions, ensuring you get competitive rates and a seamless experience from abroad.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">8.50%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Interest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹5 Crore</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Loan Amount</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">85%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Financing (LTV)</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>NRI Home Loan Interest Rates — April 2026</h3>
